      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "PARIS JAMILLA (5) overcame a second line draw when successful at her most recent outing by a neck in a nice return to form at Kilmore. Up in grade but the last time she started on the front line she came from wider than this to score last month. Big chance. THE ITALIAN DREAM (8) finished strongly to score by 4.3 metres when resuming at this venue last week. Fitter and there is no harm in drawing here with the sprint lane to rely upon so could go on with it. SHINELIKETHESUN (6) is looming as a real threat after another good effort last start, adding to a string of top-four results by finishing second at Shepparton. ARTIGAS (11) was well fancied when fresh but broke. Fitter so if he behaves a big run is likely.",
